entries.name: solid:Account
entries.description: A Solid account.

entries.name: solid:Inbox
entries.description: A resource containing notifications.

entries.name: solid:InsertDeletePatch
entries.description: A class of patch expressing insertions, deletions, and conditional modifications to a resource that has an RDF-based representation.

entries.name: solid:ListedDocument
entries.description: Listed Type Index is a registry of resources that are publicly discoverable by outside users and applications.

entries.name: solid:Notification
entries.description: A notification resource.

entries.name: solid:Patch
entries.description: A patch expresses conditional modifications to a resource that has an RDF-based representation.

entries.name: solid:Timeline
entries.description: A resource containing time ordered items and sub-containers.  Sub-containers may be desirable in file based systems to split the timeline into logical components e.g. /yyyy-mm-dd/ as used in ISO 8061.

entries.name: solid:TypeIndex
entries.description: A index of type registries for resources. Applications can register the RDF type they use and list them in the index resource.

entries.name: solid:TypeRegistration
entries.description: The registered types that map a RDF classes/types to their locations using either `instance` or `instanceContainer` property.

entries.name: solid:UnlistedDocument
entries.description: Unlisted Type Index is a registry of resources that are private to the user and their apps, for types that are not publicly discoverable.

entries.name: solid:account
entries.description: A solid account belonging to an Agent.

entries.name: solid:deletes
entries.description: The triple patterns this patch removes from the document.

entries.name: solid:forClass
entries.description: A class that is used to map an listed or unlisted type index.

entries.name: solid:inbox
entries.description: Deprecated pointer to a Linked Data Notifications inbox; please use http://www.w3.org/ns/ldp#inbox instead.

entries.name: solid:inserts
entries.description: The triple patterns this patch adds to the document.

entries.name: solid:instance
entries.description: Maps a type to an individual resource, typically an index or a directory listing resource.

entries.name: solid:instanceContainer
entries.description: Maps a type to a container which the client would have to list to get the instances of that type.

entries.name: solid:loginEndpoint
entries.description: The login URI of a given server.

entries.name: solid:logoutEndpoint
entries.description: The logout URI of a given server.

entries.name: solid:notification
entries.description: Notification resource for an inbox.

entries.name: solid:oidcIssuer
entries.description: The preferred OpenID Connect issuer URI for a given WebID.

entries.name: solid:owner
entries.description: A person or social entity that is considered to have control, rights, and responsibilities over a data storage.

entries.name: solid:patches
entries.description: The document to which this patch applies.

entries.name: solid:privateLabelIndex
entries.description: Points to an unlisted label index resource.

entries.name: solid:privateTypeIndex
entries.description: Points to an unlisted type index resource.

entries.name: solid:publicTypeIndex
entries.description: Points to a listed type index resource.

entries.name: solid:read
entries.description: Indicates if a message has been read or not. This property should have a boolean datatype.

entries.name: solid:storageDescription
entries.description: Refers to the resource that provides a description of the storage containing this resource.

entries.name: solid:storageQuota
entries.description: The quota of non-volatile memory that is available for the account (in bytes)

entries.name: solid:storageUsage
entries.description: The amount of non-volatile memory that the account have used (in bytes)

entries.name: solid:timeline
entries.description: Timeline for a given resource.

entries.name: solid:typeIndex
entries.description: Points to a TypeIndex resource.

entries.name: solid:where
entries.description: The conditions the document and the inserted and deleted triple patterns need to satisfy in order for the patch to be applied.
